simgps: A simple GPS simulator

simgps generates coordinates between two given points at a given speed and
outputs them to a serial port as NMEA sentences. At the moment, it is run
interactively from the terminal.

To run simgps you'll need:

Python 2.6
pyserial v2.5 for python2.6

This fork is for changes needed to create a GPS simulator for an AIS Transponder to be used in demo environments.
